Description: Typical range for industrial 1064 nm laser cleaning of reflective metals like manganese; starting at 200 W for contamination removal without excessive heat input. Max safe before substrate melting (Mn melting point ~1246°C) is ~1000 W with proper scanning. Source: Manufacturer specs from IPG Photonics and Coherent for metal cleaning systems; academic review in Optics and Lasers in Engineering (2018).
Near-IR wavelength for optimal absorption in Manganese oxides
Beam spot diameter for precise cleaning control
Optimal repetition rate for continuous cleaning coverage
Nanosecond pulse duration for efficient oxide layer ablation
Optimal scanning speed for uniform cleaning
Recommended number of passes for complete oxide removal
Optimal beam overlap for uniform cleaning coverage
